animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in dog who needs a new home. Adoption can be one of the most fulfilling experiences in your life and especially in the life of your new canine companion.

A note to those looking at CPR. We have no perfect dogs - but many of our dogs have proven to be perfect for a certain someone. Our job is to find those someone's. Our most successful adopters come to CPR not because they want a dog. They come to us because they want to give a dog a home. We urge all of our potential adopters not to fall in love with a picture. While we like to know what you like in looks, a dog is more than a pretty face. Our goal is to match you with the best possible pet for you and your home. We want to create furever families.

Our descriptions contain all that we know about this dog today. We'll update as more information is known.

Are you looking to adopt within the next 30 days? If so please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and complete the application. You'll find it in the menu on the left hand side. You'll also find a total listing of all our dogs available.

Just browsing but interested in poodles and poodle mixes? Please drop a note to applications@carolinapoodlerescue.org with your name, address and phone # and email. We'll add you to our mailing list.

thanks
the CPR Adoption team

Date into Rescue: 12/14/20
Reason for being in rescue: Ted was found as a stray. He was microchipped but sadly, the chip was never registered.
Foster location: Dreamweaver Farms, Pacolet SC
Special Needs? Ted was neutered and had a dental on 12/29/20. He is up to date on all vaccines and heartworm negative.
Weight: 22 lbs
Height: 14 in at the shoulder
Spayed/Neutered: Yes

Adoption Fee: $399

Fence needed? Yes

What kind of home would be best for me? Ted is a young dog that needs positive reinforcement training. He is not for an inexperienced owner and will not be adopted to first time dog owners. Ted thinks he is alpha - over humans and other dogs. This results in behavior such as humping, refusal to follow basic commands, and snarling if pushed. Ted requires a very experienced owner, committed to positive reinforcement training. He requires a home that is active - Ted needs lots of physical and mental stimulation every day.

Ted's ideal home is as the only dog with an active family that has experience with rescue and a strong commitment to training. Ted will not be placed in a home with children. He will not be placed in a home with cats or other dogs.

What is my personality like? If dogs could talk we can only imagine the stories that Ted would tell. A member of our community watched in their neighborhood as a car slowed down and a dog was let out. As the car pulled away, the dog remained. This dog was Ted, watching as his owners drove away. Thankfully the individual watching this happen scooped him up and got him to rescue. Ted was microchipped, but it was never registered. So after much effort and a stray hold, Ted is ready to start a new life!

Ted is a young dog with a big attitude. We have no history on his past, but Ted clearly ran the show. He can get snappy quickly if you stop him from doing something he is happy with or doesn't want to stop doing. He is a very smart dog who is savvy and accustomed to being the alpha. He humps to express his dominance - including other dogs and people. He loves food, but could care less about treats if he doesn't want to do something.

Ted is the type of dog that doesn't like to be put in a crate unless he goes in himself. He can be put on a leash but doesn't quite know how to walk on one just yet. He does have a lot of puppy energy and never wants to stay still. He has so much energy and life to share, but needs redirection and training to channel his energy in positive ways.

How do I act when I first meet new people? Friendly

Other tips and tidbits: We've estimated Ted's birthdate at 12/10/18. Ted was found as a stray so this is purely a guess based on his overall health and physical condition.

House trained? Dogs can be house trained if they are in the right environment and are allowed to follow a schedule as long as a physical reason doesn't keep them from being trained. A dog house trained in my home may not be in yours. We will help you teach your new dog this necessary skill and based on your schedule.

Please note - we do not ship dogs. If you are interested in adopting, please take a look at the distance between the foster home location and your location and make sure you are willing to make that trip. Most of our dogs are at our farm in Pacolet, South Carolina.

To apply, please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and visit the tab on the left that directions you to the online application.

Please note that when screening applications, we look at the entire home and then make suggestions based on what would be a good fit for your home. You are not being screened for a specific dog although we are looking to see what type of dog interests you - poodles or non poodles, color, age, etc. Others here may be a better fit for you. It is very difficult to get to know a living animal from a picture and a short description. Since we are constantly getting in new dogs, this may be a dog not in our listings yet. We want you to be very happy with your new companion and will make suggestions based on what you tell us about you.

Thank you for considering CPR.
animal.name: Ted of Charlotte

Unfortunately, I am back with GPRA. After 18 months with my previous family, I have been returned to Rescue. Why, do you ask? Well, I still have to learn how not to be possessive of my food bowl or territorial with my house and the things I want to protect. With more training, I want to overcome these issues. What else can I share…well, I am a four-year-old female that will fit best with an experienced Great Pyrenees owner or family who does not have other dogs or cats. A backyard is also recommended for me for exercise until I learn better leash manners and do not feel that I have to overprotect those walking me. I almost forgot to share with you that I am great with children and can be touched anywhere as I love my humans. Yes, I have some learning to do, but GPRA tells me that I can still be the best Pyr for a family with professional training, consistency, and patience.

Thank you for reading my story. – Millie Joy

Please email info@greatpyratlanta.com.

animal.description:
Is Pluto a planet or an asteroid? Neither, it’s me, a six-pound, eight-year-old male chihuahua! I’m fully vetted, vaccinated, neutered, microchipped, and on heartworm preventative, ready and waiting to make your life utterly heavenly!

I make up for my small size with a whole lot of love! I am always down for snuggles and prefer to sleep on top of my humans for maximum warmth and comfort. I’m also happy to cuddle with other dogs. I’m a joyful, energetic pup, and I’d love to join you for a stroll around the neighborhood. One thing is certain--when you’re around, I’ll always be in orbit!

I picked up a bad habit or two in my life before coming to the rescue, but I’m working hard to overcome them! I like having a place in the house to mark, so I'd like a potty pad I can use. Frequent trips outside help too! My vet also said I have a heart murmur, but it doesn't bother me a bit! I require daily medication for pain management and will need an experienced owner who will handle me gently. Because of this, I need to be in a home with no small children.

Despite the challenges I’ve had in life, I’m a loving and happy--not to mention handsome--little guy. I can’t wait to find my forever family and share all my affection and joy. Are you ready to meet me? Trust me, the experience will be out of this world!

If you are interested in adopting Pluto, please DO NOT SEND A MESSAGE TO OUR RESCUE GROUP.  We are too busy placing dogs in great homes to answer messages and inquiries through the listing site.  

PLEASE GO TO THE LINK BELOW TO COMPLETE AN ADOPTION APPLICATION.
 
www.chihuahua-rescue.com/adoption-application
 
CRT requires an approved adoption application and a home visit for all adoption applicants.  CRT transports to OH, KY, IL, MI, MN, WI.

animal.description:
Oakley is one of Willow's puppies!

Most of our pets are obtained from animal control and therefore we are not certain of their breed or breed mix.  We list breed mixes that they most resemble or that their former owners said they were.  However, we don't make any guarantees about breed - it is a best guess!
To meet one of our adoptable pets or to start the adoption process, please access the adoption application on our website, www.crossroadsanimalrescue.org or download and email it to crossroadsanimalrescuesc@gmail.com. We will then approve you (sending in the application does not obligate you to adopt) and we can set up a time for you to meet one or more of our pets. You can then pay the adoption fee and officially adopt after meeting your new family member. Alternatively, you can do the adoption over the phone before meeting your new pet. The benefit to this is that we will hold the pet for you. However, the adoption fee is non-refundable if you changed your mind after adopting over the phone.

Our adoption fees include the spay/neuter surgery, deworming, vet exam, and up to date vaccines. It also includes microchipping as well as heartworm testing or feline leukemia testing. We are happy to adopt out-of-state (and even out of the country!) but transportation for the adopted pet is the responsibility of the new pet owner.

If you cannot adopt a pet at this time but would like to support our rescue, please click on the "Sponsor a Pet" button. Your donation will help feed the dogs, cats, small animals, and horses at CARE.
Please email at crossroadsanimalrescuesc@gmail.com or call us at (864)972-9906 for more information. This phone number will reach Crossroads Animal Hospital, which is the home of CARE. During business hours, a receptionist will be able to speak with you regarding our adoptable pets. After business hours, the only way to contact CARE is via email. Our puppies and kittens are also eligible for 10% off the rest of the vaccines in their puppy/kitten vaccination series at Crossroads Animal Hospital. Most adult pets are spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Puppies and kittens may have the surgery before adoption or we may have new owners return later for the surgery. For more information about CARE and to see our adoption application, go to our website, www.crossroadsanimalrescue.org

animal.description:
*PLEASE NOTE:  We do not adopt out on a first-come/first-serve basis.  Applications are accepted for a puppy and then a home check is scheduled.  If there are multiple applications for a puppy, after all home checks are done, then the puppy is adopted out to the home that is the best fit for that puppy.
***** All breeds listed are a best guess or based on information from our rescue partners and are not guaranteed*****
 
 ******Chicagoland Dog Rescue reserves the right to restrict adoption of a dog to potential adopters who live within a fifty (50) mile radius of Schaumburg, IL *****

Hello out there!  My name is Corky and I am a bundle of puppy energy and just love to run around the yard with the other dogs in my foster home. I am doing really well with potty training and will go by the door when I need to go outside. I do sleep thru the night in my crate and when I need to go in the crate while my foster parents are at something called work? Not sure what that is but they come back and let me run around! I will whine and bark for a few minutes but then I get quiet and just relax. I am very friendly with people and other dogs in the foster home and just love EVERYTHING!  I’m such a happy boy. And,  my foster family says I am just adorable!  I am doing very well walking on a leash. I am not very good with cats as I like to chase them every once in a while. Because I am so people and dog friendly, I would be the perfect addition to just about any home! Like all puppies, I am looking for a lot of love, patience, and time for training so I can be AMAZING!  If you would like to meet me, please fill out a pre-adoption application and a CDR volunteer will get back to you just as quick as they can!
 XOXO
 Corky



**The ADOPTION FEE for this pet is $450 which includes getting the puppy/dog up to date on rabies, distemper and bordetella vaccines, fecal test and deworming if necessary, heartworm test, spay or neuter (not including pre-surgical bloodwork) and a microchip. Free access to our weekly training classes is also included for the life of the dog, something no other rescue in the area offers.***

animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in dog who needs a new home. Adoption can be one of the most fulfilling experiences in your life and especially in the life of your new canine companion.

A note to those looking at CPR. We have no perfect dogs - but many of our dogs have proven to be perfect for a certain someone. Our job is to find those someone's. Our most successful adopters come to CPR not because they want a dog. They come to us because they want to give a dog a home. We urge all of our potential adopters not to fall in love with a picture. While we like to know what you like in looks, a dog is more than a pretty face. Our goal is to match you with the best possible pet for you and your home. We want to create furever families.

Our descriptions contain all that we know about this dog today. We'll update as more information is known.

Are you looking to adopt within the next 30 days? If so please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and complete the application. You'll find it in the menu on the left hand side. You'll also find a total listing of all our dogs available.

Just browsing but interested in poodles and poodle mixes? Please drop a note to applications@carolinapoodlerescue.org with your name, address and phone # and email. We'll add you to our mailing list.

thanks
the CPR Adoption team

Date into Rescue: 12/19/2020
Reason for being in rescue: Stray Anderson
Foster location: Dreamweaver Farms, Pacolet SC
Special Needs? Jakob was neutered on 12/29/20. He is current on vaccines and heartworm negative. Jakob is currently being treated for ear mites. These are contaigous!
Weight: 56 lbs
Height: 24 in
Spayed/Neutered: No

Adoption Fee: $200

Fence needed? Yes

What kind of home would be best for me? Jakob is young and active with absolutely no manners. This cutie needs a very active home that is committed to training and lots of physical and mental stimulation. Jakob is a lot of dog. His energy is too much for most dogs. He could live with another dog, but it would take just the right pet. Jakob would be very happy as the only dog in your home. Jakob is not suited for a home with children under 10. He is not suited for a home with cats. JAKOB DOES SHED!

What is my personality like? Jakob is a big silly goof ball, he loves to prance around and hang his tongue out and is quite clumsy!!! He's a big puppy with little understanding of manners. He is not dog aggressive but can startle dogs if they do not match his energy, which can lead to a fight if not monitored properly. He would do well with another large rambunctious dog to show him the ropes. Jakob is a chewer, if it fits in his mouth he will chew it. He's a lot of puppy. He adores pets and cuddles. !!!!!HIGH SHEDDING!!!!!!

Jacob will "fence fight" with other dogs. We think it is less about fighting and more about wanting to get to the action and wanting to play. Jacob needs a very active home preferably with no children under 10. He likes to hug.

How do I act when I first meet new people? Friendly

Other tips and tidbits: Jakob's estimated birthday is 12/11/2019

House trained? Dogs can be house trained if they are in the right environment and are allowed to follow a schedule as long as a physical reason doesn't keep them from being trained. A dog house trained in my home may not be in yours. We will help you teach your new dog this necessary skill and based on your schedule.

Please note - we do not ship dogs. If you are interested in adopting, please take a look at the distance between the foster home location and your location and make sure you are willing to make that trip. Most of our dogs are at our farm in Pacolet, South Carolina.

To apply, please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and visit the tab on the left that directions you to the online application.

Please note that when screening applications, we look at the entire home and then make suggestions based on what would be a good fit for your home. You are not being screened for a specific dog although we are looking to see what type of dog interests you - poodles or non poodles, color, age, etc. Others here may be a better fit for you. It is very difficult to get to know a living animal from a picture and a short description. Since we are constantly getting in new dogs, this may be a dog not in our listings yet. We want you to be very happy with your new companion and will make suggestions based on what you tell us about you.

Thank you for considering CPR.

animal.description:
Willow is the sweet mom of 7 puppies, Ash, Aspen, Birch, Fir, Maple, Oakley, and Pine! Willow can't wait to meet her forever family!

Most of our pets are obtained from animal control and therefore we are not certain of their breed or breed mix.  We list breed mixes that they most resemble or that their former owners said they were.  However, we don't make any guarantees about breed - it is a best guess!
To meet one of our adoptable pets or to start the adoption process, please access the adoption application on our website, www.crossroadsanimalrescue.org or download and email it to crossroadsanimalrescuesc@gmail.com. We will then approve you (sending in the application does not obligate you to adopt) and we can set up a time for you to meet one or more of our pets. You can then pay the adoption fee and officially adopt after meeting your new family member. Alternatively, you can do the adoption over the phone before meeting your new pet. The benefit to this is that we will hold the pet for you. However, the adoption fee is non-refundable if you changed your mind after adopting over the phone.

Our adoption fees include the spay/neuter surgery, deworming, vet exam, and up to date vaccines. It also includes microchipping as well as heartworm testing or feline leukemia testing. We are happy to adopt out-of-state (and even out of the country!) but transportation for the adopted pet is the responsibility of the new pet owner.

If you cannot adopt a pet at this time but would like to support our rescue, please click on the "Sponsor a Pet" button. Your donation will help feed the dogs, cats, small animals, and horses at CARE.
Please email at crossroadsanimalrescuesc@gmail.com or call us at (864)972-9906 for more information. This phone number will reach Crossroads Animal Hospital, which is the home of CARE. During business hours, a receptionist will be able to speak with you regarding our adoptable pets. After business hours, the only way to contact CARE is via email. Our puppies and kittens are also eligible for 10% off the rest of the vaccines in their puppy/kitten vaccination series at Crossroads Animal Hospital. Most adult pets are spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Puppies and kittens may have the surgery before adoption or we may have new owners return later for the surgery. For more information about CARE and to see our adoption application, go to our website, www.crossroadsanimalrescue.org

animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in dog who needs a new home. Adoption can be one of the most fulfilling experiences in your life and especially in the life of your new canine companion.

A note to those looking at CPR. We have no perfect dogs - but many of our dogs have proven to be perfect for a certain someone. Our job is to find those someone's. Our most successful adopters come to CPR not because they want a dog. They come to us because they want to give a dog a home. We urge all of our potential adopters not to fall in love with a picture. While we like to know what you like in looks, a dog is more than a pretty face. Our goal is to match you with the best possible pet for you and your home. We want to create furever families.

Our descriptions contain all that we know about this dog today. We'll update as more information is known.

Are you looking to adopt within the next 30 days? If so please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and complete the application. You'll find it in the menu on the left hand side. You'll also find a total listing of all our dogs available.

Just browsing but interested in poodles and poodle mixes? Please drop a note to applications@carolinapoodlerescue.org with your name, address and phone # and email. We'll add you to our mailing list.

thanks
the CPR Adoption team

Date into Rescue: 11/19/2020
Reason for being in rescue: Laurens Co AC seized
Foster location: Dreamweaver Farms, Pacolet SC
Special Needs? Evie was spayed on 12/10/20. She is up to date on vaccines and heartworm negative. She's ready for her forever home!
Weight: 30 lb
Height: 18 in
Spayed/Neutered: No

Adoption Fee: $200

Fence needed? No, but she would love one. EVIE CAN NEVER BE LEFT OUTSIDE ALONE - SHE WILL JUMP OR CLIMB ANY FENCE IF UNSUPERVISED.

What kind of home would be best for me? Evie is a young dog looking for an active life. She needs a patient owner that will give her time to warm up. Once she trusts you, Evie will be your go-everywhere adventure buddy. Evie would benefit from another confident dog in the home that she can learn from. Evie can NEVER be left outside in a yard alone. She will climb or jump any fence to get to his people!

What is my personality like? Evie arrived in rescue as part of a drug bust with many siblings. We don't know what life had been like for these dogs. In general they are all younger, all timid, but all very, very sweet once they trust you.

Evie is a dog that is unsure about the world around her. She clearly hasn't had a ton of life experiences or much exposure. But underneath that timid shell is a girl that is quick to trust. Evie gets very attached to her humans very quickly. So much so, that she will scale and jump any fence to get near you.

It is not a surprise to us that Evie is great with other dogs - she has always lived as part of a pack. Dagmar is a gentle dog. She is squeaky clean in his crate, very rarely barks, and has shown no aggressive behaviors toward other dogs or people since arriving in rescue. She knows absolutely nothing about leashes, but is curious to learn.

When introduced to our office cats, Evie simply ignored them. They do not run away and are pretty blase about meeting dogs. Evie is going to make someone a great sidekick!

How do I act when I first meet new people? Shy but curious and friendly

Other tips and tidbits: Evie's estimated birthday is 11/13/2019

animal.description:
Please meet sweet puppy Leila. She is about 11 months now, 19" and 20 lbs. and will not grow any bigger.  Her story started in a very sad way with Leila found herself in a high kill shelter in the city of Pinsk (Belarus).  This shelter is one of the most cruel and inhumane places on the territory of the former USSR.  Leila was taken from the shelter by a volunteer and she flew to Moscow where other volunteers found a foster home for her.  Now Leila is a healthy and energetic beautiful puppy, up to date on all vaccines and preventives. She is a very affectionate pup, human-oriented, her favorite thing is to play with her toys and relax on a couch. Leila is curious like all puppies, loves to explore new places and ride a car. She is good on a leash, potty trained and listens to the commands.  She is good with other dogs, cats and kids. Leila is looking preferably for the one-owner dog, a woman, who is ready to give her a lot of love, care and attention and she'll pay back!

If you feel like she is the girl for you, fill out our adoption applications for her: https://forms.gle/AESXFn9Cg2gekfHUA

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

This is STU! Stu came into rescue after being dumped in a box on a rural road- covered in sarcoptic mange, and extremely malnourished and now he is a gorgeous puppy ready for adoption! Stu is house trained and is a very sweet boy that plays well with others and shares his toys nicely! He is 3 months old, around about 25lbs right now and will be a handsome medium sized boy when full grown. Stu is in a foster home in Oregon City, OR.

OUR REQUIREMENTS FOR PUPPY ADOPTION:

1) PUPPIES WILL ONLY BE PLACED IN HOMES THAT HAVE AT LEAST ONE MEDIUM TO LARGE YOUTHFUL, PLAYFUL RESIDENT DOG that is age 1 or older. This helps integrate the dog into your household easier by giving the pup a mentor.

2) These puppies are not livestock dogs. They must be family pets that are allowed inside the home.

3) In addition to the youthful playful dog, someone must also be home at least part of the day. Please do not apply for a puppy if you are gone 8+ hours a day.

4) We give preference to applicants with prior Great Pyrenees knowledge/experience.

5) Secure and visible fencing required.

6) You must have a plan in place to socialize your puppy properly.

7) Please do NOT write us and ask if this puppy is available. If it is posted, it is available. However, we may be working other applications that came in before yours. If so, by the time you are approved, the puppy may not be available.

Adoption Fee: $425

All of our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, heartworm tested and up to date on vaccinations.

Transport Fee: $300

Transport fee includes the cost of transport plus the Health Certificate required for USDA approved transport.

All of our dogs are spayed/neutered and up to date on vaccinations.

Adoption applications can be found on our website: www.greatpyrsandpaws.org

https://greatpyrsandpaws.rescuegroups.org/forms/form?formid=5959

Northwest adopter pays cost of transport to independent transport company. Transport is arranged by GPPR.

animal.description:
Meet this sweet boy named Milo James! He came into the shelter January 11, 2021 when the owner could no longer keep him. He is  unsure of shelter life ( very common with all new people, smells, other animals, & nothing familiar). We believe he was on a chain or some form of a tie out most of the time because of the calloused areas on the top of his neck and underneath his neck. We are not sure if hair will grow back but we’re going to try to help him. He is super sweet and loves being loved on and helping him feel secure. He is around 2 and a half years old, current on shots, and neutered.  He came in with 2 cats who we were told he got along well with. Also owner did say he seems to like more female dogs but doesn’t really care for make dogs. He’s such a sweet boy and I truly feel his sweetness will shine through brighter and bright once he settles in more and will even more once in a loving home where he feels safe and loved. Might you have the most amazing loving FOREVER home for sweet Milo James?! Visit with him today! 
If you have another dog and are interested in meeting another potential new furry member please bring him or her to the shelter and meet on neutral ground before adopting. No need to shuffle the animals around any more than necessary. Please know that 1 mosquito bite can create heart worms and they can be fatal if not treated. It is VERY important to keep your pets healthy and protected by keeping them on a once a month heart worm and flea/tick prevention. These animals are counting on you as their owner to provide them with lots a love and the proper health care so PLEASE make sure you are aware and prepared before adopting. Owning a pet is an extra expense and responsibility but is so worth every minute and penny you invest in them. They will add lots of joy and unconditional love if given a fair chance.
The shelter is open Mon.-Fri. 10-1, 2-5, Sat. 10-4.  Adopt a homeless pet and save a life. If you can not adopt right now come out and volunteer and make a difference in the lives of these animals while they await their FOREVER home.  
In order to adopt any of our "bully breeds" there is special paper work that will need to be collected and approved prior to the adoption.  We love all of our dogs and want to make sure to place our "bully babies" in homes best suited for them.

animal.description: Tucker is an owner surrender because his person didn't have enough time for him.  He is a big boy - 84 pounds - and carries it well!  We were told he is good with cats and other dogs and the owner's son, but he is very shy and leery of new people, especially men.  We were told that at one time a man had been very mean to him, thus the lack of trust.  Once he gains your trust, he's a different dog!  He does fine on car rides and absolutely adores our shelter worker!  With everyone else, it is very slow going - you MUST gain his trust and do it on his time!  He has a very large growl, but has never once tried to bite - even at the vet.  Tucker isn't available quite yet, but we wanted to get him posted for people to see his big beautiful face!  He is on some meds right now because of his allergies - his ears and skin need some TLC - and we're giving him medicated baths once a week for a few weeks, we'll see how that goes:)  It will take the right person for this big fella, but he will be a great addition and a real love!

animal.description:
Meet this sweetheart named Faith!  She was surrendered over to an animal control officer out in the field with the owners no longer wanted her. She has lived her life since a puppy on a chain and came in with a few sores on her head and coat of fur not in great condition. That will all change now and her future is bright. Though she does need a special home because she is deaf. Can’t imagine being alone on a chain, deaf, & so young being confined to fend yourself from the scary world out there but she did! She has played with another pup at the shelter and had fun we just have to use caution because she can’t hear warning signs if a dog is not enjoying playing or their time together. A patient home that can work with her on the basics would be great because she has spent her life outside and confines. Faith likes to chase cats so she needs a home without any cats. Faith is 1 year old, now current on shots, and so ready to begin her life with a true loving person or family who will promise to give her a loving life she deserves. She’s as beautiful as she is sweet and hopes to find her happily ever after very soon! Stop by for a visit with Faith today! 
If you have another dog and are interested in meeting another potential new furry member please bring him or her to the shelter and meet on neutral ground before adopting. No need to shuffle the animals around any more than necessary. Please know that 1 mosquito bite can create heart worms and they can be fatal if not treated. It is VERY important to keep your pets healthy and protected by keeping them on a once a month heart worm and flea/tick prevention. These animals are counting on you as their owner to provide them with lots a love and the proper health care so PLEASE make sure you are aware and prepared before adopting. Owning a pet is an extra expense and responsibility but is so worth every minute and penny you invest in them. They will add lots of joy and unconditional love if given a fair chance.
The shelter is open Mon.-Fri. 10-1, 2-5, Sat. 10-4.  Adopt a homeless pet and save a life. If you can not adopt right now come out and volunteer and make a difference in the lives of these animals while they await their FOREVER home.  
In order to adopt any of our "bully breeds" there is special paper work that will need to be collected and approved prior to the adoption.  We love all of our dogs and want to make sure to place our "bully babies" in homes best suited for them.
animal.name: Faith

animal.description:
My name is Flik! I am a 1 yr old Terrier Mix. I was adopted in June of 2020 as a healthy 4 month old puppy. Unfortunately, those horrible Wisconsin people dumped me and I was found wandering in the cold, emaciated. So here I am again! Door County has been so much fun but it is time for me to go onto my final chapter. My foster momma got me back to happy and healthy! I am spunky, silly, and extremely playful. If you have another dog I insist on it being one who loves to wrestle and be goofy. I love kids but since I'm so silly kids older than 10 would be best for me so I don't knock them down on accident. I am an expert at snuggling and love naps next to my humans. I don't have any problems with you messing with me while I eat. I know to sit for treats and am extremely good with going potty outside. I don't necessarily have a sign when I have to go out but I start pacing extremely fast trying to tell you to let me out. I know 'kennel' like a pro but I do expect a treat after I go in it. If you are interested in a cool dude like me go to sandipaws.org to fill out an application.
Thank you for your interest in a Sandi Paws Rescue, Inc. Please visit our site at sandipaws.org for more information on our organization or to fill out an application to adopt one of our pets. You can find information for volunteering o. our site as well.

animal.description:
Interested in Tinsel? Submit an application at www.pawshs.org. Petfinder inquiries will not be answered.

Tinsel is a 10# Chihuahua mix female. She is very timid, especially with new people. She is also a very picky eater and is eating chicken breast mixed in with canned and dry dog food. Chances are, she was fed exclusively ""people food"" wherever she came from. Once she bonds with you, she is very sweet and gentle but still runs from you. For that reason, we feel a fenced in yard would be safer. Tinsel was attacked by a large dog so she is uncertain around other animals and would be best as an only-dog.We also found a small bullet still lodged in her upper hind leg so this girl has been through a lot of abuse and is looking for a special home who will be patient. She does love small children so we are ideally looking for a family with a well behaved child for Tinsel to love!
We appreciate your support in helping us to find homes for our local rescues! This is how we can help lower the euthanasia rate in our county shelter. PAWS Humane Society is a local volunteer group that has helped with over 1,400 spays/neuters for the community each year through our community assistance program. We have also adopted over 600 animals during 2018. Our adoption fees include the cost of spaying/neutering, vaccinations (including rabies for cats over 4 months of age), flea prevention, worming, FeLV/FIV testing and microchipping. All PAWS Humane Society cats/kittens have been home-fostered so that you can be assured of a pet's good temperament before adopting from us. The location of our Adoption Centers: at PETCO at 6305 E. State St. in Rockford, Illinois - Forest Plaza. and PAWS at 7282 N. Cherryvale Mall Drive . Check out all of our adoptable cats and kittens on our website at www.pawshs.org. You can also contact us on our hotline: 815/299-PAWS.

animal.description:
Here is Hannah Banana! This cutie-patootie is around 35 lbs. She loves to play in the fenced in yard with her canine foster brother. She enjoys the company of dogs, people of all ages, and cats. She will need an active family because she has an enormous amount of energy! She loves walks and someone throwing a ball for her - she does not always bring it back but has tons of fun, regardless!

She is an amazing dog that did not get the best start in life, as indicated by the chain marks around her neck. Her foster family guesses she has never been indoors but is acclimating well. She is eager to please and is very food driven. The best family for her would probably have older kids because during play she jumps and may unintentionally hurt younger children. She loves attention! While playing she does growl and bark at you but her tail is going a million miles a minute, letting you know she is just a vocal girl, encouraging play. When you are trying to correct her behavior she smiles at you...teeth and all, it's actually very cute and makes it harder to be upset with her. She is house trained.
_________________________________________________________________________
Adoption Donation for Hannah is $ 425.00

WANT TO MEET Hannah

The first step would be for you to go to our website at www.aear.org and then to the ""Adopting a Pet"" page to read about our Adoption Process which will answer many of your questions and then to fill out an Adoption Application.

Also, please visit our very active Facebook Page for updates on Hannah and our other adoptable pets with AEAR - www.facebook.com/aear.org

animal.description:
Sage weighs about 50-60 pounds and is a very people friendly dog. She is definitely housebroken and has done well with the teenaged kids in her foster house. She is even friendly when meeting strangers. She is a lover and a people pleaser for sure! 
Sage does well with the other dogs in her foster house (currently she lives with an 80 lb shepherd and 15 lb chihuahua mix). The pups had a few scuffles over food between them, but no other aggression. She can be a little snappy with food but is otherwise a sweetheart. 

Sage has shown some interest in one of the cats, but doesn't chase or bark at it, even when the other dogs go crazy over the cats!

She goes to vet for her spay on January 26th, and then she will be ready for her forever home!
_________________________________________________________________________
Adoption Donation for Sage is $ 425.00

animal.description:
****PENDING ADOPTION ***

If you love decadent, delicious, and delightful desserts, then MatchDog has your dish! Welcome the Cutie Pie Pups - chock full of fluffy morsels to tempt your sweet tooth! Indulge today!

Meet BonBon! A 4-month-old female Dachsund/Chi blend WEIGHING 10 POUNDS, this bite-sized pup is super sweet and loving! Dachsunds are known for being great family dogs and even better companions. Chiuahuas make great family pets, are intelligent and loyal. True to her breeds, little BonBon fits the bill(s). She loves to play and cuddle and is great with kids and other dogs. BonBon is 80% house and crate trained and ready to find her furever home. If you think this sweet girl is your perfect match, don't delay! Apply today to make BonBon yours!

If you think you are a perfect match for BonBon please complete an application fully: https://www.petstablished.com/organization/243592

BonBon has been fully vetted, is up to date on all vaccinations and on preventatives for heartworm, flea, and tick. We cannot guarantee breed information. You will find price guidelines for adoption at matchdogrescue.org and you can read about the whole adoption process and what MatchDog Rescue provides with each dog

This gorgeous MatchDog is currently being fostered and cared for at our own facility so as to look and feel her best when she meets you on Saturday, February 13th, 2021. For the very best chance of securing a meet with this dog, you must be available all day on this date.

If you see a pending notification on this dog, it means we have informed the lucky family selected as the best match for this particular dog and they have agreed to come to the transport/event with the goal of taking the dog to their forever home. If for any reason this plan falls through, we will change the picture back to its original format and revisit other applications.

animal.description:
Hi I'm Coco! I am 
approximately 6 months old and 25 pounds so I am full of puppy playfulness and spunk! 
I started out in Texas, rode for a very long time in a bus, and found myself in this awesome place called DCHS where they are helping me search for a place to call home! This home will ideally have time to play with me, take me on walks/exploring, and teach me cool tricks. My future parents must also understand that it is very important for me to get annual dental cleanings and x-rays to monitor my oral health due to likely having a fever as a young pup so my teeth didn't form correctly. Don't let that deter you from me though, I have lots of love to give!


Placement Recommendations:
Owner Experience Level: Some Experience
Cats: Maybe/Maybe Not 
Dogs: Yes
Kids: Middle School +Want to know more? Please call us! We've found that back and forth via email regarding a specific animal is not always effective and quick because our email is not monitored on a regular basis. So, for specific information regarding this wonderful pet, please contact one of our adoption counselors at (715) 232-9790. They are available between the hours of 8 am and 7 pm (7 days a week, excluding holidays). Thanks for your interest!

animal.description: Meet Axle!! Axle is a goofy big man who just wants a fun home to call his own. Axle may be 5 years old, but he still plays like a puppy! He also loves to wiggle around and scratch his back on the couch. Axle likes his bones and food a little too much which has resulted in minor resource guarding and food aggression. With this being said, he gives plenty of warning when he feels like his bone/food is being threatened so as long as his future owners feed him in a separate location, he will do just fine. Due to his resource guarding, he will not be able to go to a home with young children (over 12 would be best). Axle does not like other dogs so he cannot go to a home with other dogs. He is house trained and crate trained. Axle is also neutered and UTD on all of his vaccines.If you are interested in learning more about this pet, call the Montgomery County, Virginia, Animal Care and Adoption Center at 540-382-5795.

animal.description:
1220120

I need a single family home since I seem to be part pittie! I can NOT go to a home in a city or county with pitbull restrictions!

My name is Murphy and my foster mom has awarded me the most improved puppy trophy. You see, my litter mates and I had a very rough start. As a result, I have had to learn some manners in order to be a good doggie citizen. My behavior has improved hugely with training and lots of love. It will be very important for me to find a forever home that can continue this training. 

I am a lab mix, who likely has some pittie in him. I am fine around cats, small dogs, and big dogs. I adore young kids and have even bonded well with special needs kids. I get a little worried around men, but have warmed up to my foster dad and I enjoy getting snuggles from him. I thrive with boundaries, training, and time. 

Due to my difficult start in life, I have suffered from malnutrition. This has affected my legs and caused them to bow. I take special vitamins for this and need to be extra careful on slippery surfaces. With vitamins, nutrition, softer surfaces, and play to help my bones get stronger, I should make a good recovery.

animal.description:
Name: Sailor
Suspected Breed(s): English Coonhound
Gender: Female
Age: 3 years
Weight: 40 lbs
Personality: Friendly, active, energetic, adventurous, snuggler, defensive, goofy,
affectionate, trainable, eager to please, shy, quiet, gentle
Observations with Dogs: Does well and enjoys greeting other dogs on walks but would do best as the only dog in the home. 
Observations with Cats: Good with cats
Observations with Kids: Gentle with kids. Sailor has been very gentle, she has been somewhat ambivalent towards kids but also when near children she has engaged in pets and snuggled.
House Training Progress: No recent accidents
Crate Training Progress: Does well in her crate
Location: DC area foster
Rescued From: Bladen County, NC
Additional Information: Sailor is a snuggly dog who enjoys the company of adults and children. She is eager to learn and please. Sailor loves to snuggle on the couch right up next to her person and is very loving and affectionate. She enjoys her crate after she is settled in. When at home Sailor prefers humans over other dogs, so she would like to be your one and only. She is learning the word sit and wants to learn some new words as well. Sailor tends to stop a lot on walks, but with a little motivation, she will go on three to four walks a day. This friendly pup is good on her leash and is unlikely to pull when she sees another dog. Sailor came to the rescue very skinny, and she is now so focused on food and that she will need training around counter surfing in the kitchen. Apply today to bring this ray of sunshine into your life.

__________________________________

If you are interested in meeting a dog or cat, we require an adoption application. If the animal has "HAS APPLICATION" listed, they are still available to receive additional applications but also may be in the process of being adopted soon. Apply for a DOG: http://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/adoptable-dogs.html

City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is a foster-based rescue in Washington, DC. We do not have a shelter. We focus on local adoptions in DC and the metro area of Maryland and Virginia. CDR&CK has a thorough adoption process in order to find the best possible fit for each of our dogs and cats (we do not operate under a first-come, first-served model).

Upon accepting a new cat or dog into the organization, we provide a basic vet visit that includes necessary vaccinations, disease screenings, deworming, microchips, and spay/neuter (unless specified). We do not provide a comprehensive medical exam prior to adoption. As a result, sickness, injury, and disability may exist unbeknownst to CDR&CK. City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is not responsible for payment of any vet care, including known and unknown medical conditions once a cat or dog is adopted from us. 
Dog specific: Rabies, DHPP, Bordatella vaccines. They are tested for HW, Lyme, Ehrlichia, Anaplasmosis.

Most cats and dogs will have a house training accident in the initial days in their new home and we cannot guarantee any pet is housebroken or crate trained.

We also update our Facebook page daily with new cats and dogs.

animal.description:
Name: Thora
Suspected Breed(s): Husky, Labrador, Shepherd mix
Gender: Female
Age: 1 year
Weight: 45 lbs
Personality: Friendly, joyful, active, energetic, playful, affectionate, calm, gentle, smart, quiet, snuggler, loyal, easygoing
Observations with Dogs: Good with other dogs
Observations with Cats: Untested
Observations with Kids: Played well during a visit to a home with a 9 year old. Thora is still learning the appropriate way to show affection; for this reason she is probably not a good match for young children until she receives more training.
House Training Progress: Working on it her anxiety about city sounds is making it hard for her to go to the bathroom outside.
Crate Training Progress: Sleeps and eats in her crate
Location: DC area foster
Rescued From: Bladen County, NC
Additional Information: Miss Thora is a sweet southern belle who is warm and cuddly. She will also run and play for hours when she feels comfortable. She has been working hard to get used to city sounds but still finds them quite scary, so she would do best with an adopter who lives in a quiet suburban area. When she is out in the open running through a big fenced yard or on a hike, Thora is very much in her element and will run and play all day - especially tug of war or fetch! If a guest comes over, Thora will greet them kindly with a few kisses and ask for a belly rub or two in return. If you have treats, shell gladly show off her sit and touch skills for you. Thora makes herself right at home wherever she is, finding the perfect comfy spot on the couch or an overstuffed chair, resting her head on a pillow, and looking at you for pets. She loves getting bear hugs from her people, and in return will try to convince them she is actually a lap dog.

Thora is sponsored and named by Samantha F in memory of her family's beloved Thunder.

animal.description:
This is Chip!

10-year-old Chip and his brother Stewie became Frosted Faces on January 12th through our Final Wish program. Their devoted pet sitter reached out to us after their owner passed away, and no one in the extended family could take them. Chip and Stewie are very friendly and sweet boys!

Chip and Stewie have gone on several hiking dates with our volunteers and have earned rave reviews for being VERY good boys! One shared, "I can't say enough good things about these two little gentlemen! They are excellent car dogs! Not a peep! Laid down, looked out the window, jumped in and out easily. We walked 2 1/2 miles and they could have gone more, especially Chip. He's part Energizer bunny! Stewie kept up, though! And just when I thought he was worn out, he came back to FFF and played fetch! They have table manners! We stopped for Wendy's before going back to FFF and got them each a plain burger. They waited patiently, never nipped, never tried to grab our own food, never once crowded us while we ate. Stewie loves cuddles and hugs, but on a walk, Chip is all business. Wanna pet him? Fine, but he doesn't care much one way or the other lol. They are clearly a well-mannered, sweet as pie, bonded pair of brothers. Any family would be lucky to have them!!"

Stop by our next Open House and meet these well-behaved and fun boys!

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

Apply to become a family: www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

Updated: 1/31/21 KG

animal.description: Joehee has had, a rough couple of months. He found himself out on his own, right before the holidays. In his picture, you will notice that his right front leg is deformed. X-rays revealed that this is a birth defect and it needs to be left alone. Joehee has no problem getting around and when he wants to run he just picks up that leg and runs on the other three. He also had to have all but two of his top teeth removed, and two nasal fistulas repaired. He is now all healed and feeling great. Joehee loves when the grandkids come and visit at his foster home, but he's just as happy when they go home. He would like a quiet home where he can sun himself on the deck, and curl up in a soft, warm bed at night.

Meet Lumpia!

Lumpia and her younger brother Brees entered San Diego Humane Society-Escondido for emergency boarding when their elderly owner became ill. When their owner went into a nursing facility, SDHS reached out to us to exit Lumpia and Brees and find them a new home together. Lumpia is 10 years and still adjusting to life without her mom; Brees is 7 years old and a happy boy. We tried to give Lumpia lots of extra loving to comfort and reassure her.

Both went to College Animal Hospital for diagnostics. While Brees is pretty healthy, Lumpia has a grade 2/6 heart murmur with severe dental disease. She has dental surgery coming up this month, and they will also try to fix her cherry eye. She has small bladder stones that we need to try to dissolve with a urinary diet, too. To help the pair decompress, we sent them to a foster home. and we are so lucky a family agreed to foster TWO Frosted Faces!

If you are looking for mellow pals who are already housetrained, you have an instant family in Brees and Lumpia! Their Foster Mom shares, "Brees and Lumpia are the sweetest! They are our first bonded pair and having the two of them together definitely makes things easier since we never have to worry about either getting lonely. They're both eager for attention, but are also fine just hanging out with each other when we're doing errands around the house. They now eat regularly morning and evening after they had a few days in our home. I was super impressed at how great they were with baths! They didn't move around at all and just took it! They both love walks. We usually take them out for about a mile morning and evening.

Lumpia (Chihuahua) is a calm, loving, patient, kinda derpy, little sweetheart. She's always trotting steadily along after Brees on walks. Although she's usually the one in the rear, she will always wait for Brees, rather than darting ahead. Brees will explore around the house and Lumpia will follow just to see what's going on and join the party. She loves meeting other dogs. She'll start RUNNING to catch up to a dog to just sniff and say hello, and then she's satisfied. She has a few health issues that we wouldn't really notice interacting with her daily, except for her smelly breath, which she's getting dental surgery for soon!

Brees (mixed spaniel) definitely acts like the youngest child. He's brave, bold, energetic, and very photogenic. He will start begging for pets if he sees Lumpia getting more attention than him. He loves playing with squeaky toys and is pretty good at fetch. He's a cuddle bug and always likes to be near you. He gets excited about seeing other dogs, but doesn't know how to properly meet them on walks. He'll just spin around a few times when he gets near them and then continues walking. Sometimes I think he's just feeding off Lumpia's excitement and copying her, but he's really a people person.

We've had so much fun with these two so far. Very loving, easy going siblings!"

Apply to meet this lovable duo at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply/

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

animal.description:
Meet Kola!

14-year-old Kola entered South LA Shelter as a stray who appeared to be in rough shape. We made Kola a Frosted Face on January 10th and took her to our vet for an exam, full body x-rays, and bloodwork. As expected, the x-rays showed severe hip arthritis and some spondylosis in the lower lumbar spine. Her lung x-rays were consistent with age. And there was really good news - her blood panel was all normal! Kola is now on pain and anti-inflammatory medications.

Kola surprised us and started following us around the lobby and tracking down toys! She also likes to work on bones. It has been so rewarding seeing her act like a dog! A wonderful vet donated some time and did acupuncture on our girl this week.

There is no better place for a dog like Kola than in a home, so we sent her off on a Frosted Fling for more individualized care. She

is enjoying the comforts of being in a home! Her Fling Mom reports that Kola is being a very well-behaved houseguest who enjoys taking naps on her cozy bed and short walks around the block. She takes her meds easily in a piece of lunchmeat and hasn't barked yet!

Check back soon for the next update on Kola's Fling!

animal.description:
Meet Admiral!

Admiral entered the South LA Animal Shelter as a stray and became a Frosted Face on January 10th! He is 7 years old and weighs 82 lbs.

Admiral is living in a Foster home, and we've learned a lot about this hunk of love! His Foster mom shares, "He's perfect. He is a dream come true. He has done nothing but smother me with love and attention and affection. He is the goofiest, sweetest, squeezy dumpkin cupcake cutie pie of a dog and that's just surface stuff. I had purchased for him a no pull harness (you know the ones with the ring in the front?) and guess who walks with a slack leash now? Also, I was noticing that he steps into my personal space when we were walking, so I gave him corrections by stepping into HIS space, and by last night he was walking alongside me like a perfect angel.

Admiral is so good with kids. ... He follows me everywhere and sits with me during zoom sessions while I work, but he will leave my side if one of the kids calls him, and he is super sweet and friendly to everyone who walks through our door. He has not met a stranger! Admiral already knows sit, and last night I showed him "down" and by the third try he did it! He doesn't chew, he doesn't bark, he takes corrections and retains them, he's just wonderful."

Other fun things we've learned about Admiral: he

loves to play with and cuddle stuffies, and t

ug of war is his favorite game. He is very gentle when taking treats, but he eats meals with such enthusiasm that a slow feeder is beneficial to keep him from inhaling his food! Although he's a big boy, he is able to hop in a SUV, no problem!

Admiral is ready for family! Apply to meet him: www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

animal.description:
Hello, my name is Bronx. My foster mom likes to call me Bonkers, I just can't imagine why! Hee hee! I have been in Minnesota since March and according to my family, I have made a lot of progress, they are very proud of me. 

When I first got here, I was afraid of everything. I'm still pretty easily spooked but if you let me come to you, I will let you pet my head and back. When I get used to you, I will put my head in your lap and ask to be petted. When we go outside together if you throw a kong or a ball for me, I will fetch it as many times as you throw it. I haven't quite figured out the part about bringing it back, but I will drop it near you. I also enjoy a good game of tug o war and am incredibly strong. 

I ADORE my resident dog and I definitely need a home where there is another dog to show me the ropes. I do have a lot of energy so might do well with someone who can keep up. My parents brought a little kitten in to our family and we became fast friends. I play with her and am very gentle. 

I am fully potty trained and will let you know when I need to go outside. I also know what it means when you say ""crate"". I will go in there and that is where I sleep.

The only concerns my family has are that I do like to chew on things so having a selection of chew toys is a good idea. Also we have not had much success with walking with a leash. I cry and whine when my brother goes on his daily walks but still don't want anything wrapped around me. Due to this and how spooked I can get, I need a fenced in yard in my new home. 

If a sweet, gentle, handsome, energetic boy is what you are looking for, I'm your guy! I can't wait to meet you!



--------------------------------------------



All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. If they came to our rescue as an owner surrender, the breed description will be listed as provided by the previous owner.

Adoption Fee - $450

To apply for this pup, please submit an Adoption Application at http://warriordogrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application/

animal.breeds_label: Belgian Shepherd / Malinois & German Shepherd Dog Mix
animal.description:
Six and a half years ago, we took a beautiful 7-week-old puppy home after not having dogs for over 30 years. Our jobs kept us from having enough time to care properly for a dog. So, in retirement, we found this beautiful German Shepherd pup from a family in Puerto Penasco, Mexico, where we live, that had been raising Shepherds for over 40 years. Diega was one of eleven puppies from a registered mom, and we were told the father could be registered but was not. As she grew and developed, it became evident to us and many around us that dad must have been a Belgian Malinois. Her temperament, coloring, and body shape seemed to confirm it. When the opportunity came to ask the owner, he confirmed it.

So here we are, two older retired folks, living on the beach, with no dog training experience, but an amazing love for this energetic puppy. She loved to run on the beach and in the desert, hunt crabs, and she is a sniffer....the best nose in Sonora! 

She is approximately 70 pounds.  She developed seizures but takes a daily gabapentin and has been seizure free for over 2 years.  She also is on a small daily dose of Incurin, a hormone.  She has been very healthy.  Additionally, she is extremely intelligent. A house without cats is highly recommended. 

We travel with her everywhere, and she developed a real love of Motel 6 and Circle K hot dogs! She's visited dog parks in several states, but her best by far was in Colorado Springs! In 2019 we traveled across the US, and she was our constant companion. 

But there were also challenges. With no experience in dog training, although she quickly learned the basic commands, her energy and need to " have a job" were unfulfilled. She has always needed a more energetic and disciplined life. We just were not knowledgeable or able to provide it. When we moved off the beach, that provided more freedom, into a residential area in Penasco, she was faced with a small yard and only leashed walks. She became much more agitated by dogs in her territory and walking became more of a challenge. When a final attack on a small dog occurred, we knew we could not provide her with what she needed.

 She loves belly and butt rubs and gets them every morning. She plays with our year-old puppy and loves to tease him with a ball or a toy. They are inseparable. My husband has too often shared a snack from the refrigerator and, if you open tuna can or a wrapped cheese slice, she's there in a nanosecond! She honestly has been my constant companion, 24/7, for all of these years. But I know that when you so dearly love an animal, you need to give them what they need, not what you need.

So the time has come to let Diega spread her wings and be the dog she can become. If you take her on, have knowledge, patience, and you will have the dog of your dreams. She has been ours!

We will require GSD/Belgian experience or the correct knowledge and lifestyle for this breed. 

https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/11077/generic

animal.description:
Courtesy Post

Biscuit, also known as Biggie, is an easy going middle aged guy (6-8) looking for a loving home.
A great companion for a person who will take him on daily walks and relax at home with him.  
He's had a rough start to life and would love to live the second half of his life in a home getting affection,  
allowed naptime on the bed or comfy chair and belly rubs.  
Good lower medium energy level boy.
Food is the key to his heart and he will reward you with a happy dance to get treats.
Has a strong sense of smell and loves to track scents.
Housetrained, just needs to be let out every few hours.
Crate trained.
Great in the car and enjoys going for rides. 
Sleeps through the night.
Not a barker at all, he's actually a very quiet guy. 
Dog friendly, but would be happy as the only dog in home, getting all of your attention.
Sorry, no cats for him.
Walks well on leash - pulls a little initially, but then prefers to walk behind his person and will not chase cats or squirrels on his walk. 
Not destructive inside or outside.
Knows commands 'sit and stay'.
Older children recommended.
Due to his previous life where he was probably starved, he has a tendency to 'inhale' his food, so a slow feeder is a good idea. 
Needs a secure fence or he will take himself out to go exploring. 
Sadly, his teeth are pretty worn down from most likely living life on a chain. 
Our best guess is that he is a Catahoula  pitty mix.
Biscuit is 66 lbs., neutered, microchipped, up to date on vaccines, including rabes, has gone through heartworm treatment and is current on prevention.

This pretty girl is Trinket! She is a 1 year old Shar-Pei/Pit Bull Terrier mix who weighs 46.8 pounds.

Trinket is friendly, cuddly, and sweet. She is a gentle girl who is shy and timid at first. She warms up quickly, but needs an adopter who will be patient while she becomes comfortable. She is young and playful, but also likes to lounge around.

Trinket is in a foster home and is doing great! While she isn't fully potty trained yet, she has already made progress and should be there in no time. She does well in her crate. Trinket definitely loves people - in fact, when she gets nervous about something, the best way to comfort her is by giving her a hug. If that doesn't show what a sweetheart she is, we're not sure what will! Trinket does jump up to give hugs, so she may knock a tiny tot over on accident. Trinket can be nervous on her leash at times and she'd love an adopter who will help her gain some confidence. No kids under the age of 10, please.

If you'd like to make Trinket your new best friend, please fill out an application to meet her! Her minimum adoption fee is $265 plus a $12 fee, if 4 months or older, for rabies registration for McLean County residents.

She has been spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm 

To fill out our adoption application, go to: http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html

animal.description:
*ADOPTER OR FOSTER NEEDED ASAP*

This incredibly handsome guy is Cricket!  Sadly, when we learned about him being at the shelter, he didn’t even have a name, so we named him Cricket.  He’s around 4 years old and is a super sweet boy who loooves people and toys, but would be best as the only animal in the home.  We need to find an adopter or foster for him ASAP.  Cricket was adopted through the rescue, but his current owner is moving and cannot take him with him.  His time is very quickly running out.  Will you help him? 

Not only is this stud muffin a big fan of toys, he also lives for going on walks.  Cricket gets so excited for his walks that he actually dances around when he sees his leash!  It’s hysterical!  He does require a lot of space to run and for someone to be loving and patient with him.  When he is not out-and-about running around or chewing on his favorite toy, there is nothing more he would prefer than to be a big ol’ cuddle bug!  This sweetness will make you want to adopt him today.  Seems to have a bit of separation anxiety, but does get used to being home alone.

Cricket does require a bull-savvy handler because of his strength and excitability.  He is an absolute sweetheart with people and is super trainable, but is leash-reactive and gets animated around other dogs/animals.  However, he can easily be redirected.  Because he is such a strong boy, would be best in a home with older children since he doesn’t know his own strength.


Please help us get Cricket into a safe, loving forever home!  If you're unable to help by adopting, sharing this post or donating is always appreciated.  Don't forget, Passion for Pitties is a 501(c)(3), so all donations are tax-deductible!…every little bit helps!
 
If you would like to adopt loving Cricket, please fill out an application at www.passionforpitties.com under the “Adorable Adoptables” heading.

animal.description:
Horatio is one suave, chocolatey colored hunk! You can tell from his soulful eyes that he has a tender, sensitive heart. He is not a boy to give it all away upfront; Horatio can seem a little timid or aloof at first, and he is all business on walks, preferring to follow his nose to the next interesting spot. But increasingly, he is showing off his affectionate and sweet side, as a sort of preview to what we think he'll be like in a home, away from all the distractions of the kennel. It seems he'll make an attentive, fond companion to his people! Back scratches in particular seem to be a quick ticket into his heart. He seems like an overall lower-key guy, though he has some strength on walks! We guess that Horatio knows to do his business outside. He is around 4 years old and weighs a sturdy 75 lbs.

Visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to set up a meet with handsome Horatio!
Due to COVID-19, CITY DOGS is currently doing adoptions by APPOINTMENT ONLY. Please visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to request a meet and greet! 

Questions? Email: citydogs@city.cleveland.oh.us | Call: (216) 664-3476
Visit: 9203 Detroit Avenue Cleveland, OH 44102

Hours:
10 AM - 3 PM Monday, Wednesday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday
10 AM - 6 pm Tuesday & Thursday

Fee: $61 | Includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, license, 30 days free pet insurance (when registered upon adoption)

The CITY DOGS mission is to increase adoptions from the City Kennel by changing the image of the pit bulls who make up the majority of the kennel population, by preparing all adoptable dogs in the kennel for lives in loving homes and by creating as many opportunities as possible for the public to meet and get to know our dogs for the terrific pets they are meant to be.

Our Adoption Process...
Here's a little about how things work:
All of the CITY DOGS posted for adoption are available for direct adoption from the kennel, unless noted otherwise. You must schedule a meet with a dog in advance - we are not currently accepting walk-ins. Please look online first to see if there are any dogs you think would be a good fit for your home before scheduling a meet. To get the process started, visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog and fill out the form. One of our adoption counselors will get in touch to schedule and confirm your meet! At the kennel, an adoption counselor will introduce you and your family to the adoptable dogs, share information we know about them, and discuss our suggested ways for successfully integrating a new dog into your home. You are welcome to meet multiple dogs. If the dog you adopt is already fixed, he or she may leave with you that day - otherwise, the dog can go home after receiving the spay or neuter surgery.)

About Our Dogs: All available dogs have gone through a behavioral and medical assessment. This assessment is a snapshot of who the dog is at that given time. We cannot make any guarantees with regard to behavior, temperament or health of any City Dog once they are in the home. Most of our dogs are picked up as strays, so we do not know what kind of home environment they were living in (i.e. with kids, other dogs or other cats), nor do we know if most of them are house trained. Everything we know about them is based on volunteer and staff observations. We do have some dogs in foster homes, where they will have more information about how the dog is in a home environment. It is very hard to tell with certainty whether or not a dog will be good with kids, cats or another dog. If you have kids in the home or another dog, we do require that they be present for a meet and greet with the dog you are considering for adoption.

Heath/Vaccinations: Dogs that are adopted directly from the kennel need to go to your personal vet within two weeks of leaving the kennel. All dogs receive their DAPPL, Rabies, and Bordatella vaccines, though you may be required to get follow up boosters. All dogs come microchipped and with a Cuyahoga County license.?

animal.description:
Snapshot of Baja Blast!

Size? I'm still growing, but I'll probably be a large pup!
Age? 3 months
Activity Level? I love playing and quiet time!
Noise Level? I rarely bark.
Good with Dogs? I would LOVE a playmate!
Good with Cats? Cats are boring, I ignore them!
Good with Kids? Older kids, if you please!
Good with Strangers? I need slow intros and space!
Potty Trained? I'm working on it!
Crate Trained?

I'm working on it!

Interested? Learn more about Baja Blast below!

About Baja Blast:

Hi! I'm Baja Blast, and I'm a sweet lab mix that came from SD about a month ago with all my siblings, and now I'm ready to look for my forever family! I have the cutest little expressive eyebrows you've ever seen! I've been spending a lot of time with my foster family and my brother, I love to play and wrestle. I am a little shy still - it takes me a little bit of time to warm up to new people, and small kiddos make me a bit nervous. But once I get to know you, I'll love you forever! I would do best in a home that has another dog to help me learn the ropes of being a confident adult pup! I'm looking for a family that will be able to keep up with my energy, but also would like to just lay around with me during nap time. And of course, someone that will be patient with me as I get comfortable in my forever home! Is that you? Apply to meet me today!

Adoption Fee: $550

Training Requirement: Obedience Level 1

*Foster to Adopt: I am looking for a forever home now, but I still need some puppy shots, and I need to be neutered on 1/29 in Minneapolis. So I'm looking for a family that will be able to commit to bringing me to all of my appointments with TCPR until I'm ready to be fully adopted by you!

MEET ME/ADOPT ME: If you'd like to arrange a meeting or begin the adoption process, please fill out an adoption application by visiting www.twincitiespetrescue.org/adopt/adopt-a-dog/ . A volunteer from Twin Cities Pet Rescue will contact you once your application is reviewed.

FOSTER HOMES NEEDED!!! Twin Cities Pet Rescue is a volunteer-run, foster home-based organization. We can only rescue as many animals as available foster homes. Please consider saving the life of an animal in need and become a volunteer foster home today. To become a foster, fill out a dog or cat foster application on the Twin Cities Pet Rescue website: www.twincitiespetrescue.org . There is little to no cost to foster an animal. Twin Cities Pet Rescue provides its foster families with food, supplies, and veterinary care for its animals. All you need to do is supply the love!

PLEASE NOTE: Twin Cities Pet Rescue does not adopt to homes further than 60 miles from the Minneapolis/St. Paul Metro Area.

animal.description: Lennon sure has captured our hearts! It is not common that a young dog has an old soul, but 2 year old Lennon most certainly has. He is a gentle, kind dog with the perfect mix of mellow energy and playful fun. He is affectionate and sweet with people - he loves to learn in for a snuggle or a sneaky kiss. When it comes to his dog friends, he's incredibly playful with other social dogs and patient and tolerant with other dogs who are learning the ropes. He has been a star of playgroup and has mixed well with both male and female dogs. Because of his social nature, Lennon may enjoy sharing his home with another friendly, social dog or may be the perfect pup for play dates with friends. Lennon is a smart boy who would love to learn new skills and tricks through positive reinforcement training. As a young dog, he may enjoy an active lifestyle as your adventure sidekick but he is also able to settle and relax when it's time to chill. Lennon was found as a stray so his history is a mystery but we know that this boy is now ready for a life filled with love, cozy beds, and tasty meals

animal.description:
OUR ADOPTION APPLICATION AND PROCESS ARE AVAILABLE AT WWW.SOHODOGRESCUE.ORG, AND OUR ADOPTION FEE IS $275

Available!
Walter is a love of a dog who is ready for adoption!  He is an Australian Shepherd mix, just 18 months old and he is a great weight at 46 pounds.  He has the most interesting merled coat with lots of white and a full tail.  Walter is housebroken, crate-trained (but not an enthusiast), and he is learning his basic obedience commands.  Walter walks pretty well on leash and is getting more comfortable riding in a car.
Walter loves people.  He is a high-Velcro, social guy who loves to do whatever his humans are doing – walk, hike, play fetch, whatever is happening!  Walter can be a little too Velcro when his foster family eats, as he is convinced that their food should be his food, but he is learning!  Walter also absolutely loves to play with other dogs, and playing chase and wrestling are his favorite dog games.  He is a medium-to-high energy boy with an “off switch”; when playtime is over he loves to snuggle and if no laps are available he will quietly chew on his favorite dog bone.  Walter is not good with cats.
The ideal home for Walter is an active one, ready to welcome a happy, friendly dog into their home.  This higher energy guy would love a fenced yard and another playful dog close to his size – he is quite the dog-wrestler!  He would also do well with a family who loves to hike and play, and who will continue his training to be an all-around great dog.  Walter still jumps on people when he is happy to see them, so children should be at least 12, and unfortunately, he cannot share a home with cats.  Walter is so smart, so happy and so ready for his forever home.  If you are ready for Walter apply today!  Walter is fostered in Atlanta, GA.

She finally arrived at her fosters at 9:30 at night in labor. At 8:30 the following morning, she delivered 6 beautiful puppies. It's her time now. She is super loving, energetic and will require an active lifestyle. Her foster has a cat she pays no attention too. 
All dogs in our program are current on all their shots and micro chipped.  Also included is one FREE group session with our amazing trainer to his Street Obedience Class is included and not to be missed.We do not place dogs on a first come first serve basis, but rather to the home best suited for them. animal.description: It was a chilly, blustery January winter’s day when Athena was given her first opportunity to experience a Humane Society bark park outing. This 11-month-old pup paid no attention to the bitter cold as she pranced and danced with her amazingly pure, from the heart, non-stop smiles gracing her face. The photographer’s fingers had become numbingly attached to his camera, but that sensation had become almost unnoticed as Athena’s buoyant, joyously playful energies brought a captivating warmth to all of the bark park participants. She would rush up to you with an unmistakable look of come-and-join-the-fun and then quickly pirouette to entice the gift of a gently taken hotdog treat. Athena performs instantaneous sits, occasionally followed by a down and then a roll over onto her back to invite a tummy touch. It was an incredibly entertaining session that lifted the spirits of all, humans and canines alike. At times, Athena seems somewhat unsure of how to interact with other dogs. We suspect that she was in an environment that didn’t provide enough socialization with other canines, but she is intelligent and really wants to please and will be a competent student.
